{\*\cs57\fs20\b\i0\expnd0\expndtw-1 motor neurons}{\fs20  (also called }{\*\cs56\fs20\b0\i efferent neurons}{\fs20 ) send neural impulses from the CNS to skeletal muscle fibers. A convenient way to remember the distinction between these neurons is to note that afferent neurons arrive at the CNS and efferent neurons exit the CNS. \line }
