{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw1 In addition to alpha motor neurons and sensory neurons, the spinal cord also contains }{\f4\fs20\b0\i\expnd0\expndtw1
interneurons.}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw1  Located primarily in the ventral horn, these interneurons are called }{\f4\fs20\b0\i\expnd0\expndtw1
Renshaw cells.}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw1  Many of the nerve fibers that descend from the brain terminate on interneurons rather than on motor neurons. These interneurons can influence the neural activity of alpha motor neurons by inhibiting the amount of activity, sometimes turning off the activity so that the neurons can fire again in a short period of time.}
{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw1 \par }\pard\plain \s18\f3\fs20\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb260\sa0\facenter\sl240\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf1\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
